/* NaCl in a water + ethanol mixed solvent.  The liquid-activity slot is the
   ELECTROLYTE-NRTL model -- selected like any activity model (one word: eNRTL).
   eNRTL is the model for a salt in a NON-ideal molecular solvent: its mixed-solvent
   term (dielectric mixing + Born) is what captures the drowning-out effect that the
   aqueous Pitzer model cannot.  The salt's ions live in NaCl.dat; ethanol's dielectric
   constant (relativePermittivity) lives in ethanol.dat -- both called by name, nothing
   chemical re-typed here.  Self-contained: components copied into constant/components/. */
components       ( water ethanol NaCl );
activityModel    { model eNRTL; }
equationOfState  { model idealGas; }
